description: From Middle English forthbringen, from Old English forþbringan (“to bring forth, produce, bring to pass, accomplish, bring forward, adduce, quote”), from Proto-Germanic *furþą (“forward, forth”) + *bringaną (“to bring”), equivalent to forth- +‎ bring. Cognate with Dutch voortbrengen (“to produce, generate, create”), German fortbringen (“to carry forth, carry away”).

verbs.description: forthbring (third-person singular simple present forthbrings, present participle forthbringing, simple past and past participle forthbrought)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To bring forth; bring out; produce.
